  "text": "Larval growth was measured as RGR under the following conditions: RGR = final weight -initial weight/(average weight/number of days) [CITATION_1] . Leaf damage was measured as the weight difference between time zero and the other timepoint. Data were analyzed using the general linear model procedure of the SAS Institute (Cary, NC, U.S.A.). When indicated, Tukey's multiple range test was used to test for differences among treatment means (at P = 0.05). Tissues (1 cm of leaf tissue immediately adjacent to the wounding site caused by insect feeding) from leaves subjected to the three types of ethylene inhibitors and controls were harvested at 0, 8, 24, and 48 h following larval feeding, were immediately placed in liquid nitrogen, and were stored at -80°C for protein and RNA gene expression analyses.",
